; extraction_mod_zones.ltx
; Safe zone definitions for Extraction Mode.
; Adapted from Fair Fast Travel (Catspaw) travel_zones.ltx structure.
;
; [zones] lists every zone section name.
; Each zone section defines one area:
;
;   level             = level name string (e.g. l01_escape)
;   owner             = faction community string  -- OPTIONAL; omit for zones open to all
;   x, y, z           = world position of the zone centre (used for entry detection)
;   radius            = detection radius in metres
;   respawn_x         = OPTIONAL; world X of the respawn point. Defaults to x (zone centre).
;   respawn_y         = OPTIONAL; world Y of the respawn point. Defaults to y (zone centre).
;   respawn_z         = OPTIONAL; world Z of the respawn point. Defaults to z (zone centre).
;   respawn_dir       = OPTIONAL; heading angle in radians (0 to 6.283). Sets the direction
;                       the player faces after respawning. Omit to leave facing unchanged.
;                       Can be set independently of respawn_x/y/z.
;                       Values: 0.0 = engine default, ~1.571 = 90 deg, ~3.142 = 180 deg, ~4.712 = 270 deg.
;                       Tip: use run_string printf("dir=%s", db.actor:direction():getH()) in
;                       the console to read your current facing and copy that value here.
;
; When respawn_x/y/z are omitted the player respawns at the zone centre.
; Override them when the centre is inside geometry, on a roof, or otherwise
; unreachable -- set them to a clear ground point inside the zone.
;
; owner values must match community strings used by game_relations:
;   stalker, army, freedom, dolg, csky, renegade, killer, ecologist,
;   monolith, bandit, greh, isg, zombied
;
; Faction ownership sourced from Fair Fast Travel travel_zones.ltx (Catspaw).
; Zones without an explicit owner are neutral -- accessible to all factions.
; Level names marked (?) are inferred and have not been verified in-game.

